            <Paragraph>
                    For the bugfix RIs, we are taking two virtual build labs (vbls) at the same time after they have passed both Build Verification Tests (BVTs) and the relevant set of quality gates. The schedule is here.
                    Getting an IDW on the code complete build ("M9") is important so we can provide that build to our development partners for them to make progress on drivers and other deliverables. IDW defines the level of quality they can expect from the build. In addition, groups outside Windows but internal to MS standardize on IDW builds for testing and development.
